33 out of 188 (18%) asymptomatic HD patients had positive naso-pharyngeal swabs for SARS-CoV-2: 23 patients in the hospital HD centre and 10 patients in the 3 satellite HD centres (Figure 3
). These COVID-19 positive patients received HD treatment in rooms together with swab-negative patients (Figure 4
) until March 25. In total, 55 out of 209 (26%) HD patients had a positive naso-pharyngeal swab for SARS-CoV-2 with or without symptoms.
